The paper deals with the problem of counting graph homomorphisms, which is a fundamental problem in graph theory and has applications in various areas of computer science. The paper presents an algorithm for solving this problem in plain exponential time for a larger class of graphs, which is a significant result in the field of computational complexity. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
